iterator

Interface Iterator<T>

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    ArrayIterator

    public interface Iterator<T>

    Iterator

    The Iterator interface declares standard methods for iterating through collections.
    Since:
    October 10 2015
    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
    Wolfy

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      T current()
      Attempts to get the current position value from the collection.
      void first()
      Sets the iterator pointer to the first element of the collection.
      boolean isDone()
      Checks whether the current position is within the iterator range.
      void last()
      Sets the iterator pointer to the last element of the collection.

    • Method Detail

      • first

        void first()
        Sets the iterator pointer to the first element of the collection. The first element is determined through the startIndex variable, specified during the initialization of the iterator object. Either first(), or last() has to be called, when the iterator is initialized.

      • next

        void next()
        Moves the iterator pointer one position to the right. Has no effect if first(), or last() was not called when the iterator was initialized.

      • previous

        void previous()
        Moves the iterator pointer one position to the left. Has no effect if first(), or last() was not called when the iterator was initialized.

      • last

        void last()
        Sets the iterator pointer to the last element of the collection. The last element is determined through the endIndex variable, specified during the initialization of the iterator object. Either first(), or last() has to be called, when the iterator is initialized.

      • current

        T current()
   throws IteratorOutOfBoundsException
        Attempts to get the current position value from the collection. If the current position is invalid, an exception is thrown instead.
        Returns:
        Returns the current position value if the current position is valid.
        Throws:
        IteratorOutOfBoundsException - An exception is thrown if isDone() returns true and current() method is called.

      • isDone

        boolean isDone()
        Checks whether the current position is within the iterator range. The range is specified during the initialization of the iterator object and is determined through the starnIndex and endIndex variables.
        Returns:
        Returns True if the current position is outside the iterator range.
